latestIgtvVideos.title: How to Style 1 Crop Top in 20 different ways
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here I am showing how to style 1 Crop Top in 20 different ways. Basically how to create sustainable fashion wardrobe. Crop top isn’t a classic yet, but has definitely been in trend over the decades, and will probably see a lot more in the future. Crop tops are like everyone's wardrobe essential. They look good on everyone from curvy to petite girls as well. They are for everyone because there are probably like a million ways you can style them.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Doodlage - They upcycle industrial waste into fun short collections
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Doodlage is a sustainable clothing startup that makes garments, accessories and home products.

Everything that we create is made out of fabric scraps sourced from large manufacturing units in India.

These fabrics otherwise add to landfills or go into incineration. Our vision is to make circular fashion mainstream.

latestIgtvVideos.title: This top is made of Soy Fabric
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
What is Soy Fabric?
This eco friendly fabric is derived from food production waste as it is made from the hulls of soy beans. Sometimes called the “vegetable cashmere”, soy is soft, easy to care for and absorbs dyes quickly, requiring less dye-stuffs.
Advantages: 
1. Echo Print 
2. Feel of fabric 
3. Moisture Absorbent
4. Anti Bacterial 
5. UV Resistant

♻️ Turn food waste into gold! 🌱

- Segregated your waste? Now, let’s compost it! 

- Use a bin with air holes. 

- Layer greens (food scraps) & browns (dry leaves/cardboard). 

- Cover & let nature do its magic! ✨ 

- Compost ready in weeks!
